60|$|The French now {{prepared}} for hostile contingencies. They launched an armed vessel of unusual size on Lake Ontario; fortified their trading-house at Niagara; strengthened their outposts, and advanced {{others on the}} upper waters of the Ohio. A stir of warlike preparation was likewise to be observed among the British colonies. It was evident that the <b>adverse</b> <b>claims</b> to the disputed territories, if pushed home, could only be settled by the stern arbitrament of the sword.|$|R
